HEADWORD: Asclepiad
<hw>As*cle"pi*ad</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Gr. & L.
Pros.)</fld> <def>A choriambic verse, first used by the Greek poet
Asclepias, consisting of four feet, viz., a spondee, two choriambi, and
an iambus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

